        },
        {
          keywords: ['what happens after', 'after i send', 'after sos sent', 'then what'],
          answer: 'After SOS is sent, the alert goes to the dispatcher side and a report ID is generated. You can use that ID to track progress on the Track page.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['safe to send', 'vehicle', 'driving', 'moving', 'car'],
          answer: 'If you are in a moving vehicle or unsafe situation, send SOS even if you cannot provide full details. Dispatch responds to the GPS location and can call your number to clarify.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['confirmation', 'did it send', 'sent successfully', 'check if sent'],
          answer: 'After tapping PANIC SOS, you should see a confirmation message or ID on screen. If not, check your internet connection and try again.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['privacy', 'data', 'security', 'tracking', 'personal info'],
          answer: 'SVS collects your location and phone number only to get help to you faster. Only authorized dispatch staff see this information to respond to your emergency.'
        }
      ],
      report: [
        {
          keywords: ['how do i report an emergency', 'report an emergency', 'how do i report', 'report incident', 'submit report'],
          answer: 'To report an emergency, open the Report page and fill in the incident details, location, and a working contact number. The form is designed to capture clearer, verified reports so dispatch can act faster.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['verify my phone number', 'verify phone', 'why phone number', 'verified contact number', 'phone verification'],
          answer: 'A working phone number helps SVS filter out prank or low-quality reports and gives dispatch a way to confirm urgent details when needed. That makes the reporting flow more reliable for real emergencies.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['what happens after i submit', 'after i submit', 'after submission', 'after report submitted', 'next step'],
          answer: 'After submission, the report is sent to the dispatcher side of SVS for review and handling. Users can then check progress from the Track page using the report ID.'
        },
        {
          keywords: ['how do i report', 'use this page', 'submit report', 'steps', 'what to do'],
          answer: 'The report page walks users through emergency type, severity, location, and scene details before submission. GPS is preferred, but barangay, landmark, and street details are also required so responders can find the incident.'
